%S A395775 1,2,2,4,5,4,6,8,6,10,12,8,14,12,10,16,18,12,20,20,12,24,22,16,25,28,
%T A395775 18,24,28,20,32,32,24,36,30,24,38,40,28,40,40,24,42,48,30,44,46,32,42,
%U A395775 50,36,56,54,36,60,48,40,56,60,40,60,64,36,64,70,48,66,72,44,60
%N A395775 The twisted Euler phi-function for the Dirichlet character kronecker(-20,.) mod 20.
%C A395775 We have h(-20*n^2), the class number of the order of Z[sqrt(-5)] with discriminant -20*n^2, is equal to 2*a(n).
%C A395775 In general, let d < 0 be a fundamental discriminant and n be a positive integer such that d*n^2 < -4, then h(d*n^2) = L(0,kronecker(d,.)) * n * Product_{p|n, p prime} (1 - kronecker(d,p)/p). This is a combination of Theorem 7.24 in "Primes of the form x^2+ny^2" by Cox and the Dirichlet class number formula. Here L(0,kronecker(-20,.)) = 2.
%D A395775 D. A. Cox, Primes of the form x^2+ny^2, Wiley, New York, 1989, p. 146.
%H A395775 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395775/b395775.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%F A395775 Multiplicative with a(2^e) = 2^e, a(5^e) = 5^e, a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p-1) if p == 1, 3, 7, 9 (mod 20) and a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p+1) if p == 11, 13, 17, 19 (mod 20).
%e A395775 Given L(0,kronecker(-20,.)) = 2, we have: h(-20*1^2) = 2*a(1) = 2, h(-20*2^2) = 2*a(2) = 4, h(-20*3^2) = 2*a(3) = 4, h(-20*4^2) = 2*a(4) = 8, ...
%o A395775 (PARI) a(n,{d=-20}) = my(f=factor(n)[,1]~, w=#f); n * prod(i=1, w, 1 - kronecker(d,f[i])/f[i])
%Y A395775 A289741 is the corresponding Dirichlet character.
%Y A395775 Cf. for fundamental discriminants -3..-24: A227128, A395768, A395771, A395769, A395772, A395773, A395774, this sequence, A395776, A395777.
%K A395775 nonn,easy,mult,new
%O A395775 1,2
%A A395775 _Jianing Song_, May 05 2026
